    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-29T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-29T00:00:00-05:00" n="87"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d87">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Sanford</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 277.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Brussels,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 29,1865.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Mourning has been brought to many families here
                    by the news from Mexico of the destruction of a detachment of the Belgian legion
                    in a combat at Tamcaburo, in the State of Michoacan, on the 11th of April. It is
                    stated in the published reports that the whole detachment of about 300 men were
                    either killed, wounded, or taken prisoners. Among the killed is a son of the
                    minister of war, General de Chazal, who was a captain, and seven other
                    officers.* *</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, with great respect, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>H. S. SANFORD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
